The Renchtalbahn is a 29.1 kilometer branch line from Appenweier to Bad Griesbach in the Black Forest.The first section between Appenweier and Oppenau was opened on June 1, 1876 by the Renchthal-Eisenbahn-Gesellschaft, which was taken over on May 31, 1909 by the Baden State Railways, which had operated from the beginning. The Deutsche Reichsbahn extended the railway on November 28, 1926 to Bad Peterstal and on May 23, 1933 to Bad Griesbach.The Ortenau S-Bahn of the SÃ¼dwestdeutsche Verkehrs-AG (SWEG) has been running on the Renchtalbahn since 1998. The trains start in Offenburg and use the Rhine Valley Railway tracks to Appenweier. ... "
